Benedictum --- Dice Roller (d6)

The fates are consulted. A number between 1 and 6 shall be revealed.

Strategy: the oracle gives 0-255. We count it down to 0, simultaneously
counting up in cell 1, resetting to 0 every time cell 1 reaches 6.
The remainder is our d6 roll (0-5), then we add 1 for 1-6.

Cell layout:
  C0 = the fate value (counts down to 0)
  C1 = the mod counter (cycles 0,1,2,3,4,5,0,1,...)
  C2 = temp (copy of C1 for comparison)
  C3 = flag (1 if C2 was 0 after subtracting 6, meaning C1 was 6)

Cast the lot.

fatum

The machine prays.

ora
    male

    dex bene sin

    Now copy C1 into C2 using C3 as a restore buffer.

    dex
    ora
        male
        dex bene
        dex bene
        sin sin
    amen

    dex dex
    ora
        male
        sin sin bene
        dex dex
    amen
    sin sin

    Subtract 6 from the copy in C2. If C2 becomes 0, C1 was exactly 6.
    If C2 wraps (becomes 250-255), C1 was less than 6.

    dex
    male male male male male male

    Set flag to 1. We will clear it only if C2 was not zero.

    dex bene sin

    If C2 is not zero, clear it and clear the flag. Loop runs once then stops.

    ora
        sanctus
        dex male
        sin
    amen

    If flag is still 1 (C2 was 0, meaning C1 was 6), reset C1.

    dex
    ora
        male
        sin sin sanctus
        dex dex
    amen

    Return to C0.

    sin sin sin

amen

C1 now holds the remainder mod 6 (range 0-5). Add 1 to get 1-6.

dex bene

Speak the die result into the light.

lux nox
